  <data key="d1">tmp_1769774017427_Large_Risk_-_Policy_Wordings</data>
  <data key="d3">61</data>
  <data key="d2">An Act of default committed by one Insured Party or its Representatives shall not prejudice
the entitlement to indemnity of any other Insured Party that has not itself (and whose
Representatives have not) committed an Act of default.</data>
</node>
<node id="sent:tmp_1769774017427_Large_Risk_-_Policy_Wordings:62">
  <data key="d0">SENTENCE</data>
  <data key="d1">tmp_1769774017427_Large_Risk_-_Policy_Wordings</data>
  <data key="d3">62</data>
  <data key="d2">In the event of the Insurer refusing to indemnify an Insured Party as a result of any Act of
default no other Insured Party shall be entitled to indemnity in respect of the same loss or
damage by assuming the rights or obligations of the Insured Party whose claim for
indemnity the Insurer has refused or is entitled to refuse.</data>
</node>
