  <data key="d3">64</data>
  <data key="d2">Material Change
As soon as is reasonably possible, any party named as the Insured in any Section of this
Policy of Insurance shall notify the Insuring Party of any Material change in risk of which it
is aware or ought reasonably to be aware and shall take or cause to be taken at its own
expense any additional precautions that may be necessary to prevent loss or damage
occurring to the Property Insured as a result of such Material change in risk.</data>
</node>
<node id="sent:tmp_1769774017427_Large_Risk_-_Policy_Wordings:65">
  <data key="d0">SENTENCE</data>
  <data key="d1">tmp_1769774017427_Large_Risk_-_Policy_Wordings</data>
  <data key="d3">65</data>
